article.headline: Army 59, Dartmouth 56
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Doug Williams scored 15 points while Marcus Nelson and Jarell Brown added 10 each as Army overcame a six-point deficit in the final nine minutes and beat Dartmouth 59-56 Saturday. Williams, who was 7-of-8 shooting, also has five rebounds, an assist, a blocked shot and a steal. Brown just missed a double-double with 10 points and a game-high nine rebounds. Dartmouth (5-6) had three players in double figures, led by Alex Barnett's game-high 20 points. Johnathan Ball netted 13 points and eight had eight rebounds, while Michael Giovacchini scored 10 points. Army (6-5) outrebounded Dartmouth, 33-25 and shot 47.8 percent for the game to Dartmouth's 37.5 percent. The Black Knights shot 76.5 percent from the foul line, scoring on 13-of-17 tries. Dartmouth scored on 14-of-19 of its free throws for 73.7 percent.
